laboratory_examinations.findings: 1.1 cm left hepatic hypodensity likely represents a cyst or hepatic hemangioma; several smaller hypodensities likely cysts; normal liver function; pancreas normal; spleen normal; kidneys normal; appendix fluid-filled and dilated up to 1.3 cm with appendicoliths and surrounding inflammatory change; trace fluid noted along right pericolic gutter; small umbilical hernia containing fat.
